The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | Formidables win
                                                                                                                       7                                      Formidables win
            A CORRESPONDENT                      
	Calcutta: Formidables of Delhi regained the Ruia Gold Cup after edging past a fighting Poddar Developers from Mumbai by 14 International Match Points (IMPs) in the final of the 52nd Winter National Bridge Championship at Netaji Indoor Stadium, here on Friday.         
	In a thrilling finish, Formidables, represented by Kiran Nadar, Subhash Gupta, K Venkatraman, B Prabhakar, R Tewari and B Satyanaryan had a slender four-point lead with two boards remaining.         
	The Delhi side managed to keep their cool and settled the issue against their Mumbai opponents 116-102 to annexe the title for the second time after 2007. Underdogs Poddar Developers were represented by NRK Moorthy, Deepak Poddar, Jitu Solani, RA Agarwal and M Athavale.         
	Hosts Bengal dominated the show in the pairs events as they bagged all but one title in these disciplines.         
	In Holkar Pairs, S N De Sarkar and Pranab Bardhan won the title after beating their city mates Sudhir Ganguly and Swapan Shome 411-402.05. The duo of D Chakraborty and D Mukherjee defeated BP Dhibar and S Banerjee by 5 IMPs to win the IMP Pairs.         
	In mixed pair, which was reintroduced after a decade, both the winners and runners-up titles went to Mumbai.         
	The husband-wife duo of Sandeep Karmarkar and Marian Karmarkar beat another husband-wife pair of Rajeev Khandelwal and Himani Khandelwal in the final.                                                                                                                     
